    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a lineup anchored by **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, who earns our highest efficiency score of 82.13. His matchup against Kelly is an ideal scenario; beyond the favorable 4.72 xERA of the starter, the 87% stolen base threat against a slow delivery, combined with wind blowing out, creates the perfect storm for his elite speed profile in our scarcity-focused build. **Junior Caminero** also projects as an elite play (75.14) against Mahle, benefiting from significant SP skill advantages and a prime #2 spot in the order. Meanwhile, **Trea Turner** (67.99) and **Colt Keith** (66.90) remain core daily drivers, with **Colt Keith** specifically gaining a boost from a favorable 94% stolen base expectancy against a sluggish delivery from the mound.\n\nWe are navigating a few tactical risks today, most notably with **Yordan Alvarez** (63.71). Despite his elite 0.430 xwOBA, the platoon disadvantage against Suarez drags his raw base projection down, though he remains an auto-start for his ceiling potential. **Kazuma Okamoto** sits at the lower end of our active spectrum (45.80) due to a difficult matchup against Ryan; while his #2 spot in the order keeps him relevant, he is the most volatile asset in today's alignment. On the bench, **Jerar Encarnacion** (41.97) was the closest candidate to displace a starter, but ultimately fell short because his platoon edge against Matz did not outweigh the higher base floor and stolen base upside of our current outfield mix. Owners should monitor the lineup status for **Hyeseong Kim** (55.99) closely, as his scoring potential is heavily suppressed by the elite hold capability of May, which restricts his stolen base opportunities\u2014the lifeblood of our offensive strategy.",
